			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I use 8 tracks; 4 for music (SqA, SqB, Tri, Nse), and 4 for sound effects (SqA, SqB, Tri, Nse). When a sound effect is triggered, its data is loaded into the appropriate track(s) depending on which channel(s) the sound effect plays on. Then, the equivalent tracks on the music side are told to mute, but they continue to &quot;play&quot; just like normal, they just don't output anything.<br /><br />When a sound effect track finishes playing, it unmutes the equivalent music track, and even restores the pitch of the current note.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

